</taxonomicName>
based on 
<specimenCount id="9D0FF2CC732BFFA19559FCC0F2A6FCE0" box="[1101,1233,768,794]" pageId="6" pageNumber="5" type="female">two females</specimenCount>
from the Mexican island of Cozumel (
<collectingRegion id="49CDF7A7732BFFA1908DFCE1F449FCC6" box="[409,574,801,828]" country="Mexico" name="Quintana Roo" pageId="6" pageNumber="5">Quintana Roo</collectingRegion>
). The male is similar to the female, differing especially by the longer antennae, which reach the middle of the elytra (basal quarter in females). Interestingly, the third specimen formally reported below was also found on an island.
</paragraph>
